.IX Title "SITAR 1"
.TH SITAR 1 "2002-09-09" "perl v5.8.0" " "
.SH "NAME"
SITAR \- System InformaTion At Runtime
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
sitar.pl       \fB\-\-help\fR
.PP
sitar          \fB\-\-help\fR
.PP
support_all.pl \fB\-\-format\fR=\fIformat\fR \fB\-\-outfile\fR=\fIfile\fR \fB\-\-help\fR
.PP
Available \fIformat\fRs: html, tex, yast1
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Prepare system information using perl, reading the /proc filesystem. Output is in \s-1HTML\s0 and LaTeX (planned: \s-1XML\s0, \s-1SQL\s0) and can be converted to PostScript and \s-1PDF\s0. Sitar is an ancient Indian instrument as well (see  \*(L"\s-1HISTORY\s0\*(R" below).
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB\-\-help\fR" 4
.IX Item "--help"
Prints a short summary of options.
.IP "\fB\-\-format\fR=\fIformat\fR" 4
.IX Item "--format=format"
Tell \s-1SITAR\s0, which output format to use. At the moment three formats are supported:
.RS 4
.IP "LaTeX" 4
.IX Item "LaTeX"
.PD 0
.IP "\s-1HTML\s0" 4
.IX Item "HTML"
.IP "YaST1\-sel" 4
.IX Item "YaST1-sel"
.RE
.RS 4
.RE
.IP "\fB\-\-outfile\fR=\fIfile\fR" 4
.IX Item "--outfile=file"
.PD
All formatted output will be stored in the file given here.
Please don't forget to give the right extension here:
\&\f(CW\*(C`.html\*(C'\fR for \s-1HTML\s0, \f(CW\*(C`.tex\*(C'\fR for LaTeX, \f(CW\*(C`.sel\*(C'\fR for YaST1\-sel\-files.
.SH "ERRORS"
.IX Header "ERRORS"
The program may \fBsilently\fR fail if either the \f(CW\*(C`/proc\*(C'\fR Filesystem does not exist or the program is not startet by the \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR user.
.SH "DIAGNOSTICS"
.IX Header "DIAGNOSTICS"
While running, stdout is redirected to the designated \f(CW\*(C`outfile\*(C'\fR file. So one will find diagnostics in this file; this (not very helpful) behaviour may change in the future.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.IX Header "EXAMPLES"
For generating a \s-1HTML\s0 documentation type as user \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR:
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`support_all.pl \-\-format=html \-\-outfile=/tmp/$HOSTNAME.html\*(C'\fR
.PP
For \s-1PDF\s0 type as user \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR:
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`support_all.pl \-\-format=tex \-\-outfile=/tmp/$HOSTNAME.tex\*(C'\fR
.PP
and twice (as an ordinary user): 
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`pdflatex /tmp/$HOSTNAME.tex\*(C'\fR
.SH "RESTRICTIONS"
.IX Header "RESTRICTIONS"
Up to now \s-1SITAR\s0 does not support \f(CW\*(C`iptables\*(C'\fR or other stuff proprietary to Linux Kernel 2.4. We are working on some of these issues.
.SH "AUTHOR"
.IX Header "AUTHOR"
The \s-1SITAR\s0 project was created by Matthias G. Eckermann <mge@suse.de>; Stephan
Müller helped with Firewalling and Security issues; Janto Trappe and Waldemar
Brodkorb created the Debian port.
.PP
For more information on \s-1SITAR\s0, see: http://sitar.berlios.de/
